{"questionId":"20258","questionHtml":"<div class=\"qb-parent-stem\"><p>A research student weighed lizard eggs in grams and recorded the results. The following&nbsp;box and whisker diagram shows a summary of the results where <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>L</mi></math> and <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>U</mi></math> are the lower&nbsp;and upper quartiles respectively.</p>\n<p style=\"text-align:center;\"><img src=\"__IMG__/ec5328eb4b5c56c791a930b3e001bf035ef428e2.png\"></p>\n<p style=\"text-align:left;\">The interquartile range is <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>20</mn></math> grams and there are no outliers in the results.</p></div>\n<div class=\"qb-leaf-prompt\"><p>Hence, find the minimum possible value of <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>L</mi></math>.</p></div>","markschemeHtml":"<p>attempt to use interquartile range &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;<em><strong>&nbsp;(M1)</strong></em></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>U</mi><mo>-</mo><mi>L</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>20</mn></math>&nbsp;&nbsp;(may be seen in part (a))&nbsp; OR&nbsp;&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>L</mi><mo>≥</mo><mn>25</mn></math>&nbsp;(accept&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>L</mi><mo>&gt;</mo><mn>25</mn></math>)</p>\n<p>minimum value of&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>L</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>25</mn></math>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;<em><strong>&nbsp;A1</strong></em></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><em><strong>[2 marks]</strong></em></p>","meta":{"questionId":"20258","referenceCode":"21M.1.SL.TZ1.4b","subjectId":"50-dp-mathematics-analysis-and-approaches","title":"Hence, find the minimum possible value of L.","paper":"1","level":"SL","questionNumber":"b","marksAvailable":"[Maximum mark: 2]","breadcrumbLabels":["Topic 4—Statistics and probability","Topic 4—Statistics and probability","SL 4.1—Concepts, reliability and sampling techniques","Topic 4—Statistics and probability","SL 4.2—Histograms, CF graphs, box plots"],"memberSectionIds":[],"sectionOrders":{}},"schemaVersion":2}